        jLabel1.setText("<html> <h1><font color='red'>Colmar Tropicale, Berjaya Hills</h1>Inspired by 16th century Colmar Village in Alsace, France, Colmar Tropicale â€“ Berjaya Hills is a four-star venture that is delightfully charming. The sprawling resort is a picturesque scene with photo-worthy hotspots dotting its landscape from the castle drawbridge and cobblestone courtyard to the cuckoo clock tower and castle moat. Featuring six different types of suites, this unique French-themed establishment boasts unique hotel facilities including a genuine Japanese village, a luxurious on-site spa and equestrian services. The hotel also has an 18-hole golf course voted one of the Top 20 Best Golf Courses in Malaysia in 2004.<br><br>Location:KM48, Persimpangan Bertingkat, Bukit Tinggi, 28750, Pahang, Malaysia<br>Contact:+609-221 3666<br>Operning Hours:Daily 24 hours<html> <h1><font color='red'>Casabrina Vacation Villas</h1>Nestled in a tranquil foothill in Pahang, Casabrina is a luxury accommodation for the weary city dweller and the environmentally conscious traveller. The entire resort was designed by owner Felix Tee and renowned Balinese architect AA Yoka Sara. Set in a natural environment, this hidden gem offers panoramic views of the lush greenery of the rainforest ~ Casabrina features two villas, Villa Aranya and Villa Amertani, with air conditioning, flat screen TVs and private bathrooms with bidets and showers. Some villas have a seating area and/or a balcony. The villas also have free Wi-Fi. Casabrina holiday villas offer guests a vast green and tranquil space surrounded by an ecological environment where exploration and adventure experiences can be experienced on a safe and guided basis. They feature many different recreational facilities, allowing residents to enjoy their leisure time.<br><br>Location:Lot 1460, Jalan Tras, Mukim Tras, 27600 Raub, Pahang,Malaysia<br>Contact:+6016-980 3222<html> <h1><font color='red'>Mutiara Taman Negara</h1>The Mutiara Taman Negara Resort has a superb rainforest setting overlooking the Tembeling and Tahan rivers. Being the only Resort inside the National Park boundary, it is an ideal place from which to explore the surrounding area. Accommodation is in comfortable Malaysian-style wooden chalets with hot and cold showers, air conditioning, television, mini-fridge, coffee & tea making facilities and ceiling fans.<br><br>Location:Mutiara Taman Negara, 27000 Kuala Tahan, Pahang, Malaysia<br>Contact:+609-266 2200<html> <h1><font color='red'>Hyatt Regency Kuantan Resort</h1>Located on the stunning beachfront of Teluk Cempedak along the east coast of peninsular Malaysia, the refurbished Hyatt Regency Kuantan Resort with 300 rooms provide a tranquil break from the city against breathtaking views of the South China Sea. Complete with family-friendly facilities, two outdoor swimming pools and a variety of restaurants and bars, the resort is the ideal spot to relax and recharge over meaningful connections that last a lifetime.<br><br>Location:Teluk Cempedak, 25050 Kuantan, Pahang, Malaysia<br>Contact:+609-518 1234");
